    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-07-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="362"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5727/75.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">British Chargé</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to your personal note of July 3, have just received from Treasury
                    Department a note stating that in view of the facts set forth, no objection is
                    perceived to the extension of the privilege requested. Copy of note in due
                    course by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
